# Snowflake Patterns — {{companyName}}

## When to Use
- Writing or optimizing Snowflake SQL queries
- Designing data warehouse schemas (star/snowflake schema)
- Managing Snowflake roles, warehouses, and access policies

## Query Patterns
- Use CTEs for readability over nested subqueries
- Leverage clustering keys for large tables
- Use `QUALIFY` for window function filtering
- Prefer `MERGE` for upsert operations
- Use `COPY INTO` for bulk data loading

## Best Practices
- Size warehouses appropriately (auto-suspend, auto-resume)
- Use resource monitors to control costs
- Implement row-level security with secure views
- Use time travel for data recovery (UNDROP, AT/BEFORE)
- Tag data assets with governance metadata
